Absent any sensible reason to condemn Hudson Yards, the vast project’s innumerable detractors came up with a laughably hypothetical one this past week.
Hudson Yards didn’t level charming old buildings or drive out poor people.
Ah, “exclusivity.”Brewer ripped Hudson Yards as “elitist” and unwelcoming to people of color.
But damning Hudson Yards is a favorite sport in the Big Apple intelligentsia’s progress-hating precincts.
Familiar gripes bleed through Kimmelman’s essay, which called The Vessel a “trash basket-shaped tourist attraction.”In the past, Kimmelman has written that he enjoyed the view from the top of Hudson Yards’ tallest building because the view didn’t include — Hudson Yards.